                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman, T</hi> 118). I searched the prisoners at the station—I found a box of composition on them, and 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 5<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. good money on Polhill, and 1<hi rend="italic">s</hi>. 4<hi rend="italic">d</hi>. on M'Donald.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18500819-name-148" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-148" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-148" type="surname" value="WEBSTER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18500819-name-148" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM WEBSTER</persName>
                  </hi>. I am inspector of coin to the Royal Mint—this shilling uttered to Evans is bad—these other two shillings are also bad, and they are all from one mould.</p>
